  { q: "What is Toronto's 180-night limit for Airbnb?", a: "Toronto caps entire-home short-term rentals at 180 nights per calendar year. This applies only to whole-unit registrations. Partial-unit registrations (renting a room while you're home) have no night limit. Many hosts fill the remaining months with mid-term bookings (30+ days) which don't count toward the cap." },
  { q: "Is it too late to start an Airbnb in Toronto?", a: "No, but the bar for success is higher than it used to be. Listings surged 23.3% year-over-year, so competition is real. However, many of those new listings are poorly optimized with phone photos and static pricing. Hosts who invest in professional photography, dynamic pricing, and guest experience still achieve strong occupancy and revenue." },
